reviewText:
Early Access Review

Used to be a big fan of the TW series, a long time ago. In my search for a decent golf sim I came across this title which is still Early Access. Normally I have developed a reluctance towards EA games, but Perfect Golf truly delivers the experience I was looking for.

> The graphics are simply beautyful. Lots of in-game tweaks possible to match the performance with your GPU setup;

> The physics in the game are almost as true as you expect them to be and truly unforgiving if your not careful;

> different swing types: 3-click, RTS, interface with various swing simulators;

> Perfect Golf has about 12 courses that are included in the download. Via internet you can easily download other courses;

> Multiplayer is fun. There are lots of possibilities to create your own or join a player/official tournament;

> The dev team is actively involved in reacting upon community feedback and improving the base game;

> Excellent price/quality ratio in my opinion.

The game has various difficulty settings. I consider myself pretty good in reading the course and circumstances, but on serious difficulties my gameplay certainly needs a lot of practise. Which is ultimately rewarding in my opinion, because the realism is so high some practice really pays off. Having delivered a devastating start in the Q-school (onlinegolftour .net) I actually feel quite happy with myself after playing 6 increasingly better rounds.

There are still things to improve (player career being one of them). But after four weeks of practicing, tournaments and playing against members of the ever growing community I am convinced this will be the best golf I ever came across.
